Ilyās ibn Yūsuf Niẓāmī Ganjavī
الياس بن يوسف نظامى گنجوى
Author dates preferred by cataloger: d. 605 AH / 1209 CE

notesStmt.note: This is an illuminated and illustrated copy of the Khamsah (quintet) by Niẓāmī Ganjavī (d. 605 AH / 1209 CE), completed by Ḥabīb Allāh ibn ʿAlī ibn Ḥusām in Safavid Iran in Rabīʿ II 971 AH / 1563 CE. Illuminated titlepieces introduce the five poems, and there are thirty illustrations, the majority of which are attributable to thirteenth century AH / nineteenth CE Qajar Iran. Ownership notes and seals indicating the provenance of this manuscript are found throughout the codex (fols. 1a, 2a, 153a, 177a, 233a, 349a, and 351a). The binding is not original to the manuscript.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Persian. The secondary language of this manuscript is Arabic.

msItem.title: Khamsah-i Niẓāmī
خمسه نظامى
msItem.incipit: بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم هست كليد در كنج حكيم...
msItem.note: Main text preceded by a biographical note on Niẓāmī (fol. 2a); consists of Makhzan al-asrār (fols. 2b-30b), Khusraw va Shīrīn (fols. 31b-108b), Laylá va Majnūn (fols. 109b-161b), Haft paykar (fols. 162b-224b), and Iskandarnāmah (fols. 225b-351a); text out of order in a number of places

colophon.note: tammat al-kitāb bi-ʿawn al-Malik al-Wahhāb bi-tārīkh muntaṣaf shahr Rabīʿ al-thānī 971 bi-khaṭṭ aqall al-anām Ḥabīb Allāh ibn ʿAlī ibn Ḥusām /1/
In Arabic, giving name of scribe and date of copying
